Components can serve multiple configurations, eg. accounts in extractors and writers, transformation buckets in transformations, orchestrations in an ochestrator, etc.

### List accounts

Lists all configurations of the current component for the given token.


GET /configs
> X-StorageApi-Token: 123456
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
[
	{
		"id": "main", 
		"name": "Main",
		"description": "Main Company Account"
	}
]

**Response attributes**
<table>
    <tr>
        <td><code>id</code></td>
        <td>Configuration Id (used in the **config** attribute in **/run** request), generated by the component when creating the configuration.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>name</code></td>
        <td>Name of the configuration</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>description</code></td>
        <td>Description of the configuration</td>
    </tr>
</table>


### Create an empty configuration table

Create an empty configuration table for the given token

POST /configs
> X-StorageApi-Token: 123456
> Content-Type: application/json
{ 
    "name": "Main"
    "description": "Main Company Account"
}
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
{
	"id": "main", 
	"name": "Main",
	"description": "Main Company Account"
}

**Request attributes**
<table>
    <tr>
        <td><code>name</code></td>
        <td>Name of the configuration</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><code>description</code> (optional)</td>
        <td>Description of the configuration</td>
    </tr>
</table>

### Delete a configuration table 

DELETE /configs/{config_id}?purge=1
> X-StorageApi-Token: 123456
< 204

**Request parameters**
<table>
    <tr>
        <td><code>purge</code> (optional)</td>
